HEADWORD: Trigeminous
<hw>Tri*gem"i*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>trigeminus</ets> born three together; <ets>tri-</ets> (see
<er>Tri-</er>) + <ets>geminus</ets> twin. Cf.
<er>Tergeminous</er>.]</ety> <def>Born three together; being one of
three born at the same birth; also, threefold.</def> <rj><au>E.
Phillip<?/.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trigenic</ent>⟦br⟧
